    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1991-01-10T12:57:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1991-01-10T12:57:00-05:00" n="188"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d188">
                <head>188. Telegram From the Delegation to the Nuclear and Space Talks in Geneva to
                    the Department of State<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d188fn1">Source:
                        Department of State, Central Foreign Policy File, Electronic Telegrams,
                        N910001–0132. Secret; <gloss target="#t_NIACT_1">Niact</gloss>; Immediate;
                            <gloss target="#t_NODIS_1">Nodis</gloss>. Sent via the Blackbird
                        channel.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">00241.</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Geneva</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1991-01-10T17:57:00+00:00">January 10, 1991, 1757Z</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_START_1">START</gloss>: Soviet Response to <persName
                            corresp="#p_BJA_1">Baker</persName> Letter</item>
                </list>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>This is Blackbird—031. Secret—Entire Text.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Late on Thursday, January 10, <persName corresp="#p_NY_1"
                            >Nazarkin</persName> called me from Moscow. He said he would return to
                        Geneva Saturday night and that his return had been delayed by working on the
                        Soviet response to Secretary Baker’s letter of January 4.<note n="2"
                            xml:id="d188fn2">See <ref target="#d185">Document 185</ref>.</note>
                    </item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_NY_1">Nazarkin</persName> said that <persName
                            corresp="#p_SE_1">Shevardnadze</persName>’s response was not yet
                        completed and he was not absolutely certain when it would be delivered.
                        Based on decisions made thus far, however, <persName corresp="#p_NY_1"
                            >Nazarkin</persName> said it <pb facs="0991" n="964" xml:id="pg_964"/>
                        was “safe to say” that the United States would be “fully satisfied” with the
                        response. In addition, <persName corresp="#p_NY_1">Nazarkin</persName> said,
                        he had spent time working on issues not included in the Houston package and
                        had been successful in getting approval to offer appropriate
                        compromises.</item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_NY_1">Nazarkin</persName> said that he hoped that the
                            <persName corresp="#p_SE_1">Shevardnadze</persName> response would clear
                        the way for high level meetings (i.e., <persName corresp="#p_BR_1"
                            >Bartholomew</persName>-<persName corresp="#p_OA_1">Obukhov</persName>)
                        in Geneva next week.</item>
                    <label>5.</label>
                    <item>I will meet <persName corresp="#p_NY_1">Nazarkin</persName> early
                            Monday<note n="3" xml:id="d188fn3">January 14.</note> and should have a
                        readout for Washington at open of business Washington time Monday
                        morning.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BRR_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Burt</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
